properties.schedule: 2nd Wednesday of every month (except July) at 3:00 p.m. The Regular Board of Equalization and Review holds its first meeting each year no earlier than the first Monday in April and no later than the first Monday in May. In a year in which a countywide reappraisal (revaluation) is not conducted, the Board must complete its duties on or before the third Monday after they begin their duties, unless in its opinion a longer period is required. However, in no event may they sit longer than July 1st. In a year in which a revaluation is conducted, the Board may sit until December 31st.
